---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const venues = [
  'Outdoor-first cafés with enough room that the dog is not an awkward afterthought.',
  'Pubs with proper beer-garden logic rather than token pet tolerance.',
  'Wineries where the outdoor setting makes sense for a longer stop, not just a quick photo.',
];
---

<BaseLayout title="Dog-Friendly Cafés, Pubs and Wineries Mornington Peninsula | Peninsula Insider" description="The Peninsula Insider guide to dog-friendly cafés, pubs and wineries on the Mornington Peninsula." section="eat">
  <main class="article-shell container prose" style="padding: 3rem 0 4rem; max-width: 820px;">
    <p class="label label--accent">Dog-Friendly Peninsula</p>
    <h1>Dog-Friendly Cafés, Pubs and Wineries on the Mornington Peninsula</h1>
    <p>A lot of venues say they are dog-friendly when what they really mean is that they will tolerate a dog if the place is quiet and you sit out of the way. That is not the same thing as a venue that actually works when the dog is part of the plan.</p>
    <p>The better dog-friendly venues have space, outdoor logic, enough airflow between tables, and staff who do not look surprised when a water bowl is requested.</p>
    <h2>What qualifies</h2>
    <ul>
      {venues.map((venue) => <li>{venue}</li>)}
    </ul>
    <p>This should become a properly verified working list. The right editorial standard is practical usefulness, not token inclusion.</p>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
